news.title: ACC's net profit dips 59.70% in Q3 FY23
news.para: ACC's total consolidated income stood at Rs 4,577.66 crore in Q3 FY23, a growth of 4.52 per cent from Rs 4,279.64 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Sunteck Realty's net profit dips 81.46% in Q3 FY23
news.para: Sunteck Realty's total consolidated income stood at Rs 97.46 crore in Q3 FY23, a growth of 27.68 per cent from Rs 134.77 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Housing prices beginning to firm up after two-year covid lull: Economic Survey
news.para: ​India's residential market has witnessed recovery this fiscal on pent-up demand with increase in housing sales despite impediments like rising interest rates on home loans and appreciation in property prices, said the Survey which was tabled in Parliament.

news.title: Simpliwork Offices invests Rs 40 crore on two centers in Kolkata
news.para: Simpliwork Offices aims to grow by 2.5 times by the end of March 2024 and expects to add another 4 lakh sq ft in the next three years in Kolkata.

news.title: Orient Cement's net profit dips 37% in Q3 FY23
news.para: Orient Cement's total income stood at Rs 733.42 crore in Q3 FY23, a growth of 18.29 per cent from Rs 620 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Budget 2023: The Wadhwa Group's Navin Makhija wants higher relief on the home loan rates
news.para: Navin Makhija, managing director, The Wadhwa Group anticipate the government to announce incentives that will propel the growth of the sector such as introducing tax breaks which will increase public spending, less transaction cost, etc in Budget 2023.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh to come up with code for green buildings
news.para: The state was working on the general guidelines laid down under the National Building Code. Going forward the UP government will frame a specific set of rules and framework to recognise energy efficient buildings after floating specific building norms that have to be adhered to.

news.title: Budget 2023: MYRE Capital's Aryaman Vir wants separate section for home loan principal repayment deduction
news.para: The government should consider increasing the maximum loss that can be claimed as a deduction for income under house property in the upcoming budget 2023, says Aryaman Vir, founder & CEO, MYRE Capital.

news.title: Mohali civic body seals 11 properties for non-payment of taxes
news.para: The enforcement wing of the civic body here on Monday went on to seal 14 properties, but three out of them paid the property tax on the spot and were let off.

news.title: Budget 2023: Real estate industry demand infra status, clarity on input tax credit
news.para: Real estate industry stakeholders are hoping that the upcoming Union Budget 2023 will provide the much needed push which will help continue the growth momentum, the industry has witnessed.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body may raise property tax rates
news.para: Sources said for the last decade while the Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation (AMC) did not increase property tax rates outright, when it linked the tax to jantri rates, effective rates paid had risen.

news.title: Budget 2023: Shyam Steel's Lalit Beriwala wants enhanced outlay in capital investment in infrastructure
news.para: Extension of the provision of low tax rate of 15% introduced by the Government of India under Section 115BAB of the Income Tax Act for new manufacturing companies who start commercial production by 2024 till 31st March 2025, said Lalit Beriwala, director, Shyam Steel Industries

news.title: Over 1,600 EWS flats in Delhi's Jailorwala Bagh likely to be completed by March: DDA
news.para: A senior DDA official said 1,675 flats for Economically Weaker Sections (EWS) are being constructed for this JJ cluster and the work is likely to be completed by March.

news.title: Mindspace REIT's net operating income rises 22% to Rs 455 crore in Q3 FY23
news.para: Mindspace Business Parks REIT said in a regulatory filing that its gross leasing stood at 1.3 million square feet in the third quarter of FY23, taking cumulative leasing during April-December to 3.5 million square feet.

news.title: Home registrations in Kolkata jump 61% since stamp duty sop
news.para: However, the registrations in December 2022 was lower by 17% against December 2021. Homes of less than 500 sqft took the biggest hit with registrations down 33% in a year.
